  "texts": [
    "For each fold, the testing of each model was done in the left-out connectome (Table S1).",
    "Statistical tests and p-value computations were done with Scipy's stats module and in-house permutation scripts.",
    "Unless stated otherwise, we used one-tailed hypotheses only when addressing the significance of strictly positive magnitudes combined with non-parametric methods.",
    "Nonnegative magnitudes cannot be tested for negative results and do not need to satisfy normality.",
    "The Leave One Out cross-validation approach yielded a pool of 19 subjects that were independently tested."
